node.text: 49ers’ QB Trey Lance has a small "chip" in his finger and is expected to miss about a week, per HC Kyle Shanahan.

node.text: Colts placed quarterback Carson Wentz, center Ryan Kelly and wide receiver Zach Pascal on the Reserve/COVID-19 list.

node.text: First of many cuts this week is a notable one: Lions have released WR Breshad Perriman, per source. Lions' top four wide receivers now shape up to be Tyrell Williams, Amon-Ra St. Brown, Quintez Cephus and Kalif Raymond.

node.text: Colts’ HC Frank Reich on WR T.Y. Hilton’s neck injury: “It was a disc issue, so that's a complicated issue. More meetings, more evaluation to come, more opinions to come….He will miss some games, we don't know exactly how many. We're optimistic it's not season-ending.”
